news.title: Pune residents want action against officials for permitting constructions on floodlines
news.para: Recent floods near the Mula and Mutha rivers in Pune have reignited concerns over poorly defined red and blue lines, leaving residents worried about their properties. Citizens are demanding accountability from officials for allowing construction in flood-prone areas, highlighting the administrative confusion and lack of coordination between local bodies and the irrigation department.

news.title: Chandigarh admin directs CHB to install firefighting system at Dhanas rehabilitation colony
news.para: Punjab Governor Gulab Chand Kataria has directed the Chandigarh Housing Board to urgently install a firefighting system at the Dhanas Rehabilitation Colony, where over 45,000 residents have been without adequate fire safety for 13 years. Despite mandatory requirements and repeated requests, the system is missing, raising concerns about resident safety and compliance with the National Building Code.

news.title: Draft Punjab building rules worse than land pooling: PAC
news.para: Ludhiana residents are protesting the Draft Punjab Unified Building Rules 2025, fearing increased traffic and overcrowding. A public action committee argues the rules prioritize developers' profits over citizen well-being. They demand an extension for submitting objections, citing concerns about unlimited floor area ratio (FAR), increased densities, and inadequate fire safety measures.

news.title: Consumer forum orders DLF to compensate buyer for delay in handover of flat in Kakkanad
news.para: The Ernakulam district consumer commission has directed DLF to compensate a customer for a nearly four-year delay in handing over a flat in Kakkanad. The developer was also found guilty of charging additional fees and providing substandard quality. DLF must pay interest on the flat's price, refund rent expenses, and provide compensation for distress and court costs.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC summons Bhopal collector in contempt case
news.para: The MP High Court has summoned Bhopal collector Kaushlendra Vikram Singh on August 25 due to a contempt petition. This petition was filed because of non-compliance with a court order to execute a revenue recovery certificate (RRC) for Rs 70 lakh from a builder, issued by RERA.

news.title: Brigade Group leases nine-acre land in Chennai's OMR
news.para: Bengaluru's Brigade Group has secured a long-term lease for nine acres in Chennai. The land is located in Perungudi along Old Mahabalipuram Road. This acquisition from YMCA allows Brigade to develop 1.6 million sq ft. Plans include a Grade-A office complex and a 200-key JW Marriott hotel. This move significantly expands Brigade's commercial and hospitality presence in Chennai.

news.title: Microchip picks up office space in Bengaluru for ₹176 crore
news.para: Microchip Technology, through its Indian arm, has acquired 1.72 lakh sq ft of office space in Whitefield, Bengaluru, for ₹176 crore. The purchase from Ascendum Solution India includes two commercial blocks in the EPIP Zone. This significant transaction, valued at ₹10,230 per sq ft, marks one of the largest office space buyouts in the city this quarter.

news.title: Fit-outs now key revenue engine for flexible offices
news.para: Flexible workspace operators are increasingly benefiting from office fit-outs, which have become a significant revenue stream. India's cost-effective fit-out market, coupled with rising demand for customized workspaces, attracts businesses. Companies like Awfis and Carbon Guardians are expanding their fit-out services, driven by growth in gross leasing and the expansion of global capability centers, contributing significantly to their revenues.

news.title: Owners in Goa to be fined for not providing tenant information
news.para: The Goa government is drafting rules to fine property owners who fail to provide tenant information, inviting public input before implementation. These rules, under the Goa (Verification of Tenants) Act, 2024, aim to enhance security by verifying tenant details. Penalties for non-compliance could reach Rs 10,000, with police intensifying verification drives due to Goa's high tourist influx.

news.title: Rollout of new building bylaws hits roadblocks in some cities in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: New building bylaws in Uttar Pradesh face implementation hurdles as housing authorities seek clarification on parking standards for hotels, open space calculations, and allowing hospitality on agricultural land. Several cities, including Varanasi and Ayodhya, are grappling with issues related to narrow roads and the conversion of residential properties to commercial use.

news.title: Hydraa reclaims ₹400 crore worth prime land in Madhapur
news.para: Hyderabad's Hydraa reclaimed a prime 3.3-acre land parcel worth ₹400 crore in the IT corridor, a decade after its alleged encroachment by businessman Jaihind Reddy. The agency demolished an illegally built restaurant and hoardings following local complaints, freeing up parks, roads, and government land. A police case has been registered against Reddy for trespassing and violating public property laws.

news.title: Gurugram RWAs seek reduction in GST on maintenance bills from 18% to 5%
news.para: Resident Welfare Associations in Gurugram are appealing to Haryana CM Nayab Singh Saini to reduce the GST on monthly maintenance bills from 18% to 5%, arguing that essential services like security, water, and sanitation should not be taxed as luxury items.

news.title: DTCP issues notice to Experion Developers, RWA for flouting layout rules in Gurugram
news.para: The DTCP has issued a show-cause notice to Experion Developers and the Windchants RWA in Sector 112 for violating the approved layout plan. Deviations include converting fire tender paths into green areas and selling setback land. The developer and RWA must remove the violations and provide a written explanation, or face legal action.

news.title: Expedite welfare housing projects for poorer sections: Andhra Pradesh CM to officials
news.para: Andhra Pradesh CM Naidu has set an ambitious goal to complete 10 lakh welfare houses by March 2026, prioritizing housing for the poor. He directed officials to categorize projects for efficient execution and identify homeless families, allocating land in rural and urban areas.

news.title: Prime minister to inaugurate PMAY houses in Gujarat
news.para: Narendra Modi will visit Gujarat starting August 25. He will inaugurate houses and shops built under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana. The project aims to rehabilitate slum dwellers. Gujarat has sanctioned many houses under this scheme. The state government provides additional assistance to beneficiaries.

news.title: ED says Vasai-Virar ex-civic chief, co-accused perpetrated high-value fraud, misused powers
news.para: Anil Pawar, ex-chief of Vasai-Virar, and three others are in jail for money laundering. The Enforcement Directorate (ED) found misuse of power and the financial system. Hawala channels moved illegal funds across states. Sitaram Gupta and Arun Gupta, builders, are also accused. They built illegal structures in Vasai-Virar. The court has sent all four to judicial custody.

news.title: NeoLiv acquires 17.5-acre land in Mumbai region
news.para: Realty firm NeoLiv is set to develop a housing project in Khopoli, Mumbai Metropolitan Region, after acquiring 17.5 acres of land. The company will invest ₹150 crore to develop around 180 plots and villas. This marks NeoLiv's third project, following the successful sale of plots in Haryana and a luxury housing project in Alibaug.

news.title: Kerala government nod to raise 1,500 crore as loan for LIFE Mission housing
news.para: The Kerala cabinet has approved a Rs 1,500 crore loan for the LIFE Mission housing scheme, with funds allocated for ongoing construction and housing assistance for Scheduled Caste and Tribe beneficiaries. Additionally, the cabinet approved Onam gifts for elderly Scheduled Tribe members, bonus guidelines for PSU employees, and new teaching posts in nursing colleges.

news.title: Varanasi development body allocates 82 houses under PMAY
news.para: The Varanasi Development Authority (VDA) allocated 82 houses under the Prime Minister's Housing scheme through a lottery held at Girija Devi Cultural Complex. The allocation, involving houses in Harhua and Kurhua villages, was conducted transparently among 642 beneficiaries.

news.title: Trichy civic body to upgrade 3,250 dim streetlights at ₹2 crore
news.para: Trichy Corporation is set to upgrade 3,250 streetlights from 20-watt to 40-watt LEDs in residential areas, addressing residents' complaints about insufficient lighting. The ₹2 crore project will prioritize junctions and densely populated areas, with each ward receiving 50 upgraded lights. However, councillors are expressing concerns that the allocation is inadequate to meet the needs of all areas.
